              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Upper Limit of Statistical Standard Deviation",
                "For Errors Arising from the Number of Events."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The Uncertainty is Shownon Figures by Authors.",
                "Two Systematic Errors were Important.  One Arose",
                "In Obtaining the Solid Angle to Derive the Absolute",
                "Cross Section, by Tracing Particles Through the Magnet",
                "System, Using a Monte Carlo Calculation and a Classical",
                "Optical Method. Uncertainties in this Calculations May",
                "Give Rise to Errors of As Much As 50% in the Absolute",
                "Cross Sections.",
                "The Other Occurred in Calculating the Scattering",
                "Correction For the Detector System.  This Could be As",
                "Large As 20% For Protons Emitted with 100- MeV, But  is",
                "Already Very Small For 400-MeV Protons.",
                "These Two Errors have No Effect on the a-Dependence,",
                "Since this is a Ratio."
              ]
            },
